modules.description: Parses command-line arguments into a key-value store, supporting flags and positional arguments. It works with strings and maps key-value pairs from raw input. Used to extract configuration parameters from boot arguments in MirageOS projects.

Splits a string into a list of substrings based on whitespace, preserving quoted sections using backslashes. Accepts a single string input and returns a result type with either the parsed list or an error message. Used to process command-line arguments or configuration strings with embedded quotes.
